cess\nrelationship: part_of GO:0030210 ! heparin proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0050650 ! chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0050651 ! dermatan sulfate proteoglycan biosynthetic process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28977\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29294\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30378\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: sjm\ncreation_date: 2024-11-27T13:13:42Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0120562\nname: GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol mannosyltransferase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the transfer of a mannosyl residue to GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol bearing 0-8 mannoses during synthesis of the N-glycan precursor.\" [GOC:curators]\nsubset: gocheck_do_not_annotate\nis_a: GO:0000030 ! mannosyltransferase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30326\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: sjm\ncreation_date: 2025-05-28T07:19:38Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140100\nname: lytic exotransglycosylase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the exolytic cleavage of the (1->4)-beta-glycosidic linkage between N-acetylmuramic acid (MurNAc) and N-acetylglucosamine (GlcNAc) residues in peptidoglycan, from either the reducing or the non-reducing ends of the peptidoglycan chains, with concomitant formation of a 1,6-anhydrobond in the MurNAc residue.\" [EC:4.2.2.n1]\nsynonym: \"murein lytic endotransglycosylase E activity\" NARROW []\nxref: EC:4.2.2.n1 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0008933 ! peptidoglycan lytic transglycosylase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/21167\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-02-05T12:50:17Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140263\nname: keratan sulfate-I proteoglycan bio