{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778977080506,"sessionID":"ses_1ccbbf94effeJuWf8Ry3Dh7s3w","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ip4WCx6DI9YhjNWP1XvvT0Q8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_35536957.md","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_35536957.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:35536957\n3: title: The O-GlcNAc Modification.\n4: authors:\n5: - Varki A\n6: - Cummings RD\n7: - Esko JD\n8: - Stanley P\n9: - Hart GW\n10: - Aebi M\n11: - Mohnen D\n12: - Kinoshita T\n13: - Packer NH\n14: - Prestegard JH\n15: - Schnaar RL\n16: - Seeberger PH\n17: - Zachara NE\n18: - Akimoto Y\n19: - Boyce M\n20: - Hart GW\n21: year: '2022'\n22: doi: 10.1101/glycobiology.4e.19\n23: content_type: abstract_only\n24: ---\n25: \n26: # The O-GlcNAc Modification.\n27: **Authors:** Varki A, Cummings RD, Esko JD, Stanley P, Hart GW, Aebi M, Mohnen D, Kinoshita T, Packer NH, Prestegard JH, Schnaar RL, Seeberger PH, Zachara NE, Akimoto Y, Boyce M, Hart GW\n28: **DOI:** [10.1101/glycobiology.4e.19](https://doi.org/10.1101/glycobiology.4e.19)\n29: \n30: ## Content\n31: \n32: 1. The O-GlcNAc Modification.\n33: \n34: Zachara NE, Akimoto Y, Boyce M, Hart GW.\n35: \n36: In: Varki A(1), Cummings RD(2), Esko JD(3), Stanley P(4), Hart GW(5), Aebi M(6), \n37: Mohnen D(7), Kinoshita T(8), Packer NH(9), Prestegard JH(10), Schnaar RL(11), \n38: Seeberger PH(12), editors. Essentials of Glycobiology [Internet]. 4th edition. \n39: Cold Spring Harbor (NY): Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory Press; 2022. Chapter 19.\n40: \n41: Author information:\n42: (1)Distinguished Professor of Medicine and of Cellular & Molecular Medicine, \n43: Co-Director, Glycobiology Research and Training Center, University of \n44: California, San Diego, La Jolla, California, USA\n45: (2)Professor of Surgery, Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, Director, \n46: National Center for Functional Glycomics, Harvard Medical School, Boston, \n47: Massachusetts, USA\n48: (3)Distinguished Professor of Cellular & Molecular Medicine, Co-Director, \n49: Glycobiology Research and Training Center, University of California, San Diego, \n50: La Jolla, California, USA\n51: (4)Horace W. Goldsmith Foundation Chair, Professor of Cell Biology, Albert \n52: Einstein College of Medicine, Bronx, New York, USA\n53: (5)Sr. Eminent Scholar in Drug Discovery, Georgia Research Alliance William \n54: Henry Terry Professor of Biochemistry & Molecular Biology, Complex Carbohydrate \n55: Research Center, University of Georgia, Athens, Georgia, USA\n56: (6)Professor of Mycology, ETH Zürich, Institute of Microbiology, Department of \n57: Biology, Zürich, Switzerland\n58: (7)Distinguished Research Professor, Georgia Athletics Association Professor in \n59: Complex Carbohydrate Research, Professor of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology, \n60: Complex Carbohydrate Research Center, University of Georgia, Athens, Georgia, \n61: USA\n62: (8)Endowed Chair and Professor, Yabumoto Department of Intractable Disease \n63: Research, Research Institute for Microbial Diseases, Immunology Frontier \n64: Research Center, Osaka University, Osaka, Japan\n65: (9)Distinguished Professor of Molecular Sciences, Macquarie University, Sydney, \n66: Australia and Principal Research Leader, Institute for Glycomics, Griffith \n67: University, Gold Coast, Australia\n68: (10)Professor and Eminent Scholar Emeritus, Complex Carbohydrate Research \n69: Center, University of Georgia, Athens, Georgia, USA\n70: (11)Professor, Departments of Pharmacology and Neuroscience, Johns Hopkins \n71: University, Baltimore, Maryland, USA\n72: (12)Director of Max-Planck-Institute of Colloids and Interfaces, Potsdam, \n73: Germany, Professor, Freie Universität, Berlin, Germany\n74: \n75: This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or \n76: threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins \n77: by O-linked β-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-β-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc. This \n78: seemingly simple carbohydrate modification plays key roles in cellular \n79: physiology and disease progression. Underpinning these observations are the \n80: thousands of O-GlcNAc-modified (O-GlcNAcylated) proteins that regulate cellular \n81: processes, such as epigenetics, gene expression, translation, protein \n82: degradation, signal transduction, mitochondrial bioenergetics, the cell cycle, \n83: and protein localization.\n84: \n85: Copyright © 2022 The Consortium of Glycobiology Editors, La Jolla, California; \n86: published by Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory Press; \n87: doi:10.1101/glycobiology.4e.19. All rights reserved.\n88: \n89: DOI: 10.1101/glycobiology.4e.19\n90: PMID: 35536957\n\n(End of file - total 90 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:35536957\ntitle: The O-GlcNAc Modification.\nauthors:\n- Varki A\n- Cummings RD\n- Esko JD\n- Stanley P\n- Hart GW\n- Aebi M\n- Mohnen D\n- Kinoshita T\n- Packer NH\n- Prestegard JH\n- Schnaar RL\n- Seeberger PH\n- Zachara NE\n- Akimoto Y\n- Boyce M\n- Hart GW","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_35536957.md","time":{"start":1778977080496,"end":1778977080505}},"id":"prt_e334c04ab001Eyc5PJkNHSle54","sessionID":"ses_1ccbbf94effeJuWf8Ry3Dh7s3w","messageID":"msg_e334bf353001n3QwHoyxkWYo6s"}}
