{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778977593563,"sessionID":"ses_1ccbbf94effeJuWf8Ry3Dh7s3w","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_2Vr7tFSazzdLjb3BT9J3i7hA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+# Research for GO issue #32044\n+\n+## PMID:35536957 \"The O-GlcNAc Modification.\"\n+\n+This chapter from Essentials of Glycobiology supports creating a BP term for protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine. It describes O-GlcNAc as a dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl groups on proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, also termed O-beta-GlcNAc or O-GlcNAc.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-beta-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc.\"\n+\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO issue #32044\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+Create a new biological process term for `protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine`.\n+\n+## Existing precedent\n+\n+No DOSDP YAML pattern specific to protein O-linked glycosylation via sugar was found in `src/patterns`. Existing GO precedent under `GO:0006493 protein O-linked glycosylation` uses direct asserted subclass terms for specific initiating sugars, without `intersection_of` logical definitions:\n+\n+* `GO:0016266 protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine`\n+* `GO:0035269 protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose`\n+* `GO:0180059 protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose`\n+* `GO:0180062 protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose`\n+* `GO:0180063 protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose`\n+* `GO:0180064 protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose`\n+\n+## Modeling decision\n+\n+The new term follows the established sister-term pattern: a `biological_process` term with a definition stating the O-linked initiating sugar, an asserted `is_a: GO:0006493`, requested exact synonyms, term tracker metadata, and creation metadata.\n+\n+No `intersection_of` logical definition was added. The existing sister terms do not use logical definitions, and adding one here would introduce inconsistency without a documented design pattern.\n+\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@\n+# Research for GO issue #32044\n+\n+## PMID:35536957 \"The O-GlcNAc Modification.\"\n+\n+This chapter from Essentials of Glycobiology supports creating a BP term for protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine. It describes O-GlcNAc as a dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl groups on proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, also termed O-beta-GlcNAc or O-GlcNAc.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-beta-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc.\"\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO issue #32044\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+Create a new biological process term for `protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine`.\n+\n+## Existing precedent\n+\n+No DOSDP YAML pattern specific to protein O-linked glycosylation via sugar was found in `src/patterns`. Existing GO precedent under `GO:0006493 protein O-linked glycosylation` uses direct asserted subclass terms for specific initiating sugars, without `intersection_of` logical definitions:\n+\n+* `GO:0016266 protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine`\n+* `GO:0035269 protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose`\n+* `GO:0180059 protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose`\n+* `GO:0180062 protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose`\n+* `GO:0180063 protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose`\n+* `GO:0180064 protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose`\n+\n+## Modeling decision\n+\n+The new term follows the established sister-term pattern: a `biological_process` term with a definition stating the O-linked initiating sugar, an asserted `is_a: GO:0006493`, requested exact synonyms, term tracker metadata, and creation metadata.\n+\n+No `intersection_of` logical definition was added. The existing sister terms do not use logical definitions, and adding one here would introduce inconsistency without a documented design pattern.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","relativePath":"RESEARCH.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@\n+# Research for GO issue #32044\n+\n+## PMID:35536957 \"The O-GlcNAc Modification.\"\n+\n+This chapter from Essentials of Glycobiology supports creating a BP term for protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine. It describes O-GlcNAc as a dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl groups on proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, also termed O-beta-GlcNAc or O-GlcNAc.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:35536957 \"This chapter presents an overview of the dynamic modification of serine or threonine hydroxyl moieties on nuclear, mitochondrial, and cytoplasmic proteins by O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine, termed O-beta-GlcNAc or simply O-GlcNAc.\"\n","additions":7,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO issue #32044\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+Create a new biological process term for `protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine`.\n+\n+## Existing precedent\n+\n+No DOSDP YAML pattern specific to protein O-linked glycosylation via sugar was found in `src/patterns`. Existing GO precedent under `GO:0006493 protein O-linked glycosylation` uses direct asserted subclass terms for specific initiating sugars, without `intersection_of` logical definitions:\n+\n+* `GO:0016266 protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetyl-galactosamine`\n+* `GO:0035269 protein O-linked glycosylation via mannose`\n+* `GO:0180059 protein O-linked glycosylation via glucose`\n+* `GO:0180062 protein O-linked glycosylation via galactose`\n+* `GO:0180063 protein O-linked glycosylation via arabinose`\n+* `GO:0180064 protein O-linked glycosylation via xylose`\n+\n+## Modeling decision\n+\n+The new term follows the established sister-term pattern: a `biological_process` term with a definition stating the O-linked initiating sugar, an asserted `is_a: GO:0006493`, requested exact synonyms, term tracker metadata, and creation metadata.\n+\n+No `intersection_of` logical definition was added. The existing sister terms do not use logical definitions, and adding one here would introduce inconsistency without a documented design pattern.\n","additions":22,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the followin